snippet: Delegates from the International Criminal Court on Tuesday visited colleagues being held in Libya over allegations that they had smuggled documents to Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi’s detained son.
abstract: Delegation from the International Criminal Court visits its colleagues being held in Libya over allegations that they had smuggled documents to Seif al-Islam el-Qaddafi.
lead_paragraph: Delegates from the International Criminal Court on Tuesday visited colleagues being held in Libya over allegations that they had smuggled documents to Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi’s detained son.

headline.main: Libya: World Court Delegation Visits Detained Staff
